  <text>
    <body>

      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>Four <rs key="marmor">blue-grey marble</rs> fragments (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.15</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.975</measure> (total) × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.20</measure>) which join, from the crowning feature of a <rs>balustrade</rs>; the top is smooth; one side has a moulded profile, the other is smooth, tapering inwards. The underside has been left rough. Resembles <xref type="inscription" n="93" href="010013">1.13</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="94" href="010014">1.14</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="95" href="010015">1.15</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="96" href="010016">1.16</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> in one line on upper <term>fascia</term> of moulded profile.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p><measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.035-0.04</measure>; elongated, lunate.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date notAfter="0600" exact="none" notBefore="0401">Fifth to sixth centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">location</rs>, <rs type="criteria">script</rs>).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
		<ab>
		<lb n="1"/><persName key="Gabriel" type="divine" full="yes"><num><gap dim="left" reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><unclear reason="damage">ι</unclear>ὴλ</num></persName> <w lemma="βοηθέω">βοήθησον</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῖς</w> <w lemma="δοῦλος">δούλοις</w> <w lemma="σύ">σου</w> <persName type="aphrodisian" key="theodoretus1" full="yes"><name reg="Θεοδώρητος">Θεοδωρήτῳ</name></persName> <w lemma="καί"><expan><abbr>κ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αὶ</supplied></expan></w> <persName key="Cyriacus1" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Κυριακός">Κυριακῷ</name></persName> <g type="cross"/> <g type="leaf"/> <space dim="horizontal"/>
		</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab><gap dim="left" reason="lost"/>iel help your servants Theodoretos and Kyriakos</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="VII.10">VII.10</xref>.</p>
        
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p>Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Temple/Church</rs>: Three fragments found in sectors xv and xiii, str. 1; one stray find.</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation"><rs type="monuList">Temple/Church</rs>: <seg cert="low">Crowning the chancel barrier</seg>.</rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="lastLocation">Museum.</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

      <div type="history" n="record">
        <head>History of Recording</head>
        <p>Excavated by the NYU expedition in 1962 and 1968 (<rs type="invNo">62.100</rs>, <rs type="invNo">62.111</rs>, <rs type="invNo">68.292</rs>).</p>
      </div>

